{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":" works like a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticMutexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be statically allocated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". In these cases you can also use a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It must be initialized with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()"},{"text":" can also be used even if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"isAc